----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Added concrete resources PatientData and Queue with owner/access constraints to fix type errors in acceptance/reachability predicates.
-- Summary 2: Added fifth permission Urgency5 to align with requirement urgency levels 1-5; updated stronger function and edge case assertion ec_safe_1.
-- Summary 3: Fixed ac_reach_1, ac_reach_2, ac_reach_3 to correct resource references (PatientData, Queue) and fixed ac_reach_3 accessibility check.
-- Summary 4: Fixed ec_safe_3 to reference Queue resource instead of interface.
-- Summary 5: Preserved all original structure, comments, and run/check commands; model is now consistent and executable.
-- Assumption 1: Permissions Read, Write, Execute, Admin, Urgency5 map to urgency levels 1-5 respectively, though the spec does not enforce this mapping; it is used for authorization checks.
-- Assumption 2: PatientData resource represents patient medical records; Queue resource represents the waiting queue; both are owned by Triage_Nurses with appropriate access.
-- Assumption 3: The operation REQ_TRIAGE_01 encapsulates both database update and queue recalculation via separate post-states Post1 and Post2.
-- Assumption 4: Simultaneous assignments on the same resource are allowed only if initiator and grant match (edge case ec_safe_2).
-- Open issue 1: The nfr_assert_usability assertion (all interfaces same kind) contradicts the defined interface kinds (Database vs API); it will likely fail and is a modelling proxy that may need refinement.
-- Open issue 2: The stronger function is defined but not used in any constraint or assertion; it may be removed or integrated into authorization logic.
-- Open issue 3: Edge case 2 (simultaneous assignments) uses a restrictive condition (same initiator and grant) that may not cover all realistic concurrency scenarios; the model does not include time or event ordering.


